RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 6 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOUBLE PRIORITY went to the early lead into the first turn then settled off the pace on the backstretch, regained the lead at the quarter pole and drew clear into the stretch, was kept to task in the drive and held on. CALLEN FEELS GOOD raced near the back going into the first turn then made a rail bid on the backstretch, moved out to two path at the end of the bend but was not enough. IDE LIKE HAWAII settled in the middle of the pack from the two path down the backstretch then move out to three wide mild bid on the final turn, moved out to four to five wide in the stretch to be a game third. JOEY'S LIGHTENING was unhurried around the first turn then move out to five wide at the five sixteenths pole to make a bid, moved in to three wide on the final turn and passed tiring rival. MONITOR MILLS hopped at the start then rushed up to vied for the lead on the inside took the lead on the first turn to the quarter pole and weakened. MISCHEVIOUS ROBERT raced in the middle of the pack from the three path but was not a threat. TOOCAN DANCE pressed the pace from the three path around the first turn then tracked the leaders from the three path to the five sixteenths pole and gave way.

ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, rail bid, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Monitor Mills
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, rushed up, led briefly, weakened,

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEXICAN WONDER BOY was roused to take the lead and set the pace from the inside, dug in entering the stretch, drifted out and brushed with SEAU in mid stretch but drew clear. SEAU vied for the lead from the two path through the final turn then was brushed by MEXICAN WONDER BOY in mid stretch, had to steady slightly and proved second best. MILITARY BEARING was reluctant to load into the gates, then was allowed to settle while saving ground to the final turn then moved out to three wide in upper stretch and made a late gain. DUST EM was four wide into the first turn then pressed the pace from the three path to the three sixteenths pole and gave way. JOCKEY OBJECTION, JOCKEY OF SEAU CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF MEXICAN WONDER BOY FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN MID STRETCH, AFTER A STEWARD REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED.
